<refnamediv>
<refname>setuidgid</refname>
<refpurpose>runs another program under a specified account's uid and gid.</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<cmdsynopsis>
<command>setuidgid</command>
<arg choice='req'><replaceable>account</replaceable></arg>
<arg choice='req'><replaceable>child</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection><title>Description</title>
<para>
<replaceable>account</replaceable> is a single argument.
<replaceable>child</replaceable> consists of one or more arguments. 
</para>

<para>
<command>setuidgid</command> sets its uid and gid to <replaceable>account</replaceable>'s uid and gid, removing all supplementary groups.
It then runs <replaceable>child</replaceable>.
</para>

<para>
<command>setuidgid</command> cannot be run by anyone other than root.
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection><title>Exit codes</title>
<para>
<command>setuidgid</command> exits 111 if it cannot find a UNIX account named <replaceable>account</replaceable>, if it cannot setgid, if it cannot setuid, or if it cannot run <replaceable>child</replaceable>.
Otherwise its exit code is the same as that of <replaceable>child</replaceable>.
</para>
</refsection>

